The paper discusses a solution for optimizing large-scale analytics, which is a common problem in the field of database systems (cs.DB). The solution relies on Machine Learning (ML) to provide approximate answers to aggregate queries, which falls under the category of ML (cs.LG) and AI (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of benchmarks to evaluate the capabilities of the system, which is a common practice in the field of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and distributed computing (cs.DC).
